items.title: Pinwheel Launches Kid-Friendly Smartwatch with AI Chatbot
items.summary:
- The *Pinwheel Watch* is a smartwatch for children aged 7-14, designed to be a safe alternative to smartphones.
- It features parental controls, GPS tracking, and **PinwheelGPT**, an AI chatbot tailored for kids, which avoids inappropriate content.
- Available for $160 with a subscription, the watch emphasizes *safety* and *supervision*, allowing parents to monitor interactions and set usage limits.

items.title: Castelion Raises $350M Series B for Hypersonic Missiles
items.summary:
Castelion, a startup focused on *hypersonic weapons*, has successfully secured a **$350 million Series B** funding round.  
- The funding, led by *Lightspeed Venture Partners*, pushes the company's valuation into the billions.  
- Castelion aims to disrupt the defense market by rapidly developing and *vertically integrating hypersonic missile systems*.  
- The upcoming Blackbeard Ground Launch project could lead to significant contracts and deliverables by early 2028, intensifying competition with major defense players.

items.title: xAI gets permits for 15 natural gas generators at Memphis data center
Ransomware Gang Hunters International Announces Shutdown
items.summary:
- The *Hunters International* ransomware gang is shutting down and offering free decryption keys to impacted victims.
- Recent developments hint at a potential rebranding to *World Leaks*, suggesting a strategy to evade law enforcement scrutiny.
- Analysts believe this move may be a gesture of goodwill as the gang shifts to a new infrastructure to avoid detection.

items.title: Tighten Up Your Cap Table at TechCrunch All Stage 2025
items.summary:
- *Fundraising* is challenging; a messy *cap table* complicates it further.
- The event on *July 15* will feature experts discussing *cap table best practices* for effective fundraising.
- Attendees will learn how to prepare and present a clean cap table, avoiding common delays and costs in the fundraising process.

items.title: Writer CEO May Habib to take the AI Stage at TechCrunch Disrupt 2025
items.summary:
- May Habib, CEO of Writer, will feature in a *fireside chat* at TechCrunch Disrupt 2025, discussing how enterprises are operationalizing AI at scale and speed.  
- Writer's AI agents are transforming industries like financial services, clinical research, and e-commerce with *domain-specific language models* through clients such as Uber, Intuit, and Vanguard.  
- The session will delve into real-world deployment, responsible scaling of AI agents, and the future of enterprise AI from experimentation to execution, attended by over 10,000 startup and VC leaders.

items.title: Everything about Flashes: Bluesky's Instagram alternative
items.summary:
- Flashes is a new photo-sharing app built on the Bluesky social network, offering an Instagram-like experience with scrollable feeds, photo filters, and user portfolios integrated with Blueskyâ€™s 37 million users.  
- It supports posting up to 4 images and videos up to 3 minutes long, and interactions like likes, reposts, and replies sync with Bluesky. Users can customize profiles and browse specialized Bluesky feeds on topics or media formats.  
- Developer Sebastian Vogelsang plans to add subscriptions, push notifications, multi-account support, longer videos, Stories, and more, evolving Flashes into a standalone AT Protocol platform while maintaining Bluesky compatibility.

items.title: Israeli quantum startup Qedma just raised $26 million, with IBM joining in
Google rolls out its new Veo 3 video generation model globally
items.summary: - Google has launched its **Veo 3 video generation model** to Gemini users in over *159 countries*, available to AI Pro subscribers. - The model allows generation of videos up to *8 seconds* long using text prompts, with a daily cap of 3 videos. - Google is also working on expanding Gemini to include **image-to-video generation** capabilities soon.

items.title: AI job predictions become corporate Americaâ€™s newest competitive sport
items.summary:
- *Top executives* are making increasingly *dramatic predictions* about AI causing massive job losses, especially in white-collar roles.
- These forecasts, including claims that AI could replace **half of all U.S. white-collar workers**, have become part of a *competitive narrative* among CEOs.
- The rising severity of these predictions suggests that *massive restructurings* and significant employment impacts are imminent, regardless of initial cautious statements.

items.title: French B2B fintech Qonto reaches 600,000 customers, files for banking license
French B2B neobank Qonto reaches 600,000 customers, files for banking license
items.summary:
- Qonto, a French fintech targeting European freelancers and SMBs, has filed for a **banking license** to expand its lending, savings, and investment offerings, aiming to grow beyond its 600,000 customers towards 2 million by 2030.  
- Currently operating with a payment institution license, Qonto's profitability achieved in 2023 allows it to pursue this without additional fundraising, differentiating it from competitors and enhancing independence from third-party financing services.  
- The license would unlock new revenue streams and enable faster product development, including AI features, while strengthening risk managementâ€”all part of Qonto's strategic maturation and potential IPO groundwork.

items.title: OpenAI Condemns Robinhood's 'OpenAI Tokens'
items.author: Maxwell Zeff
items.summary:
- **OpenAI** publicly disavowed Robinhood's sale of 'OpenAI tokens', clarifying they are not equity and were not approved by OpenAI.
- Robinhood offers these tokens as indirect exposure to OpenAI shares via ownership in a special purpose vehicle (SPV), but tokens are not direct stock ownership.
- The move raises concerns about private company equity representation, with **OpenAI warning consumers to be cautious** of the token sales.

items.title: Wonder Dynamics Co-founder Nikola Todorovic Joins AI Stage at TechCrunch Disrupt 2025
items.summary:
- Nikola Todorovic, a visual effects veteran and co-founder of Wonder Dynamics (now Autodesk), will speak at TechCrunch Disrupt 2025 about the convergence of AI and creative filmmaking.  
- He helped develop Autodesk Flow Studio, a pioneering AI platform that automates complex visual effects processes, enabling faster, more accessible film production.  
- At Disrupt, Todorovic will discuss AI's impact on media, generative tools, ethical design, and the future of creator workflows with other AI experts.

items.title: Lucid EV Sales and Production Progress
items.summary:
*Lucid delivered 3,309 vehicles in Q2, marking a 6% increase and setting a new sales record.*
- The company produced 3,863 vehicles, nearly 1,000 more than the previous quarter, but still faces a significant gap to reach its 20,000 annual target.
- To meet its goals, Lucid is ramping up production of the all-electric Gravity SUV, despite facing supply chain bottlenecks and slow start issues, with company CEO emphasizing quality over speed.*

items.title: Substack brings new updates to livestreaming as it increases video push
Could Google's Veo 3 be the start of playable world models?
items.author: Rebecca Bellan
items.summary:
- Googleâ€™s Veo 3 model, capable of generating video and audio simulating real-world physics, hints at future potential for *playable world models* in video games.  
- Currently a passive generative model, Veo 3 could evolve into an *interactive, predictive simulator* possibly combined with other Google models like Genie for richer game environments.  
- This move positions Google against rivals like Microsoft, OpenAI, and others in the race to create *AI-driven video game worlds* and immersive gameplay experiences.

items.title: Founder-Focused Approach to Anxiety at TechCrunch
items.summary:
- *Startup founders face constant emotional swings due to decision-making and pressure.*
- Dr. David H. Rosmarin will lead a session on **transforming anxiety into a strategic advantage** at TechCrunch All Stage 2025.
- Key takeaways include **channeling pressure into better decisions, building resilience, and embracing anxiety as a tool** for leadership success.

items.title: Lovable aims for $150M funding, $2B valuation
items.summary:
- *Lovable*, a fast-growing European AI startup, is planning to raise over *$150 million* at a *$2 billion* valuation, as reported by the *Financial Times*. 
- Since its launch in 2023, the company quickly scaled, hitting *$50 million* ARR within six months and raising a *$15 million* seed round earlier this year. 
- Lovable offers a platform that builds *web apps* from *text prompts*, with new features like an AI agent for automating tasks, adopting a *usage-based* pricing model, echoing the trends in *AI-driven business models*.

items.title: Amazon to Shut Down Freevee App in August 2025
items.summary:
- Amazon will discontinue its stand-alone Freevee app by August 2025, encouraging users to watch Freevee content on *Prime Video* instead.  
- This move consolidates Amazonâ€™s streaming services, transitioning content including *free originals* and licensed shows to a single platform without changing availability.  
- Freevee, launched as IMDb TV in 2019 and rebranded in 2022, reflects Amazonâ€™s strategy to simplify offerings amid growing streaming dominance over cable and broadcast TV in the U.S.

items.title: Teslaâ€™s energy storage business gets sucked into the companyâ€™s downward spiral
Indiaâ€™s Max Financial says hacker accessed customer data from its insurance unit
Perplexity launches a $200 monthly subscription plan
TikTok Lays Off More Employees in US Shop Unit
items.summary:
- *TikTok Shop US*, launched less than two years ago, is facing difficulties despite being TikTok's fastest-growing business.
- The company has conducted its *third round of layoffs* since April, with details undisclosed, indicating struggles in its US operations.
- Meanwhile, *regulatory issues persist* as President Trump delays and discusses potential TikTok sales, involving possible buyers with VC backgrounds, affecting TikTok's future in the US.

items.title: Terra CO2 secures $124M to reduce concrete emissions
items.summary:
- *Terra CO2* raised **$124.5 million** in Series B funding to develop a *low-carbon cement alternative*. 
- Their *supplementary cementitious materials* (SCM) can replace up to **40%** of traditional Portland cement, reducing COâ‚‚ emissions by **70%**. 
- *Investors* like **Breakthrough Energy Ventures** and **Al Gore's Just Climate** support efforts to *decarbonize* the *building materials industry*.

items.title: ChatGPT's Growing News Referrals & Industry Impact
items.summary:
*Referrals from ChatGPT to news sites have increased 25-fold, yet they can't offset *declining search traffic*.**

*Since Googleâ€™s AI Overviews launch, no-click news searches have risen from 56% to 69%, leading to a drop in organic traffic from 2.3 billion to under 1.7 billion visits.*

*While some sites, like Reuters and NY Post see increased ChatGPT referrals, overall publisher traffic suffers, prompting experiments with paywalls and new monetization strategies.*

items.title: Former SpaceX manager alleges harassment, retaliation, and security violations in lawsuit
items.summary:
*A former SpaceX security manager alleges discrimination, sexual harassment, and retaliation.*
- Jenna Shumway claims her work environment changed after a senior employee, Daniel Collins, was hired, leading to harassment and her eventual termination.
- The lawsuit highlights issues of *security protocol violations* and previous reports ignored by SpaceX, amid ongoing investigations into the company's security practices.

"*Allegations suggest systemic issues within SpaceX's work environment and security protocols.*"

items.title: A guide to using Edits, Metaâ€™s new CapCut rival
items.summary:
- *Meta* released **Edits**, a new short-form **video editing** app targeting creators, as a competitor to *CapCut*. 
- The app offers various tools like **green screen**, **timelines**, **captions**, and **AI-powered** features, and is available on **iOS** and **Android**. 
- While Edits currently has fewer advanced features and a smaller music library than CapCut, it is free and may add paid options and web support in the future.

items.title: US chipmakers could see bigger tax credits if Trumpâ€™s spending bill passes
items.summary:
*The semiconductor industry may benefit from increased tax credits if the current spending bill passes.*  
*The proposed bill would raise the tax credit for U.S. chip manufacturing plants from 25% to 35%.*  
*This boost aims to support U.S. chipmakers like Intel, TSMC, and Micron amid recent export restrictions affecting revenues.*

items.title: Meta Verified Support Fails During Ban Wave
items.summary:
- *Meta's paid verification service*, introduced in 2023, promised *direct customer support* but has largely failed during a *mass ban wave* affecting Instagram and Facebook accounts.
- Users report *dismissive and unhelpful support* from Meta, with many facing *erroneous suspensions* and difficulty in resolving issues, leading to significant *personal and business losses*.
- Meta has only acknowledged the *Facebook Group ban issue*, with little detail or updates on the *AI or malware-related* causes, leaving users frustrated and in the dark about the resolution process.

items.title: Data Breach Exposes Catwatchful Stalkerware Spying on Thousands
items.summary:
- A security flaw in the *Catwatchful* Android spyware leaked 62,000 customer emails and passwords and data from 26,000 victims, revealing widespread illegal surveillance.  
- The spyware masquerades as a child monitoring app but steals private data including photos, messages, live location, and microphone/camera feeds, often installed without victim consent.  
- The breach exposed the operator's identity and database hosted on Google Firebase, prompting Google to enhance Play Protect and investigate the spyware's violation of terms.

items.title: Hacked, leaked, exposed: Why you should never use stalkerware apps
items.summary:
- The stalkerware industry, which markets apps for illegal surveillance on partners and family, has been repeatedly hacked or suffered massive data leaks, exposing millions of victims' personal information.  
- Since 2017, at least 26 stalkerware companies have been compromised, revealing sensitive data such as messages, photos, and GPS logs, while some companies have shut down or rebranded following breaches.  
- Experts warn these apps are unethical and illegal, urging users to reject stalkerware in favor of transparent and secure parental control tools, emphasizing the grave privacy risks and potential abuse associated with these insecure spyware products.

items.title: Microsoft will lay off 9,000 employees, or less than 4% of the company
Tesla faces second straight year of falling sales after another bad quarter
Rivian Receives $1B from Volkswagen Amid Sales Decline
items.summary: - Rivian secured $1 billion from Volkswagen due to a joint venture and reaching a gross profit milestone, despite a 23% drop in Q2 2025 vehicle deliveries compared to the previous year. - The EV startup expects to deliver 40,000 to 46,000 vehicles in 2025, lower than prior years, while facing increased costs from US tariffs and trade tensions. - Challenges persist with tightening federal EV tax credits and heavy financial losses, placing pressure on Rivian ahead of the 2026 release of its affordable R2 SUV.

items.title: Foxconn tells hundreds of Chinese staff to return from its Indian iPhone factories
Qantas Hack Exposes Data of 6 Million Passengers
items.summary:
- Australian airline *Qantas* experienced a **data breach** compromising personal details of at least 6 million passengers, including names and frequent flyer numbers.
- The attack targeted a call center on June 30, stealing data like emails, phone numbers, and dates of birth.
- The breach is part of a growing trend of airline cyberattacks, potentially linked to the hacker group *Scattered Spider*, known for sophisticated intrusions.

items.title: Jon McNeill brings the operatorâ€™s playbook to TechCrunch All Stage
Congress approves NASA moon plan opposed by Musk and Isaacman
items.summary:
*The U.S. Senate approved a bill increasing NASA funding for the Artemis program, including $10 billion for rockets and lunar station.*
- This decision opposes critics like Elon Musk and Jared Isaacman, who favor reusable and alternative technologies over the traditional SLS rocket.
- The funding contradicts NASA's previous proposal to phase out the SLS, signaling strong political backing for existing legacy aerospace projects despite criticisms.*

items.title: ICEBlock App Goes Viral After Bondi Criticism
items.author: Zack Whittaker
items.summary:
- ICEBlock is an iPhone app that allows users to anonymously report sightings of U.S. ICE agents, gaining viral popularity after U.S. Attorney General Pam Bondi's critical remarks.
- Originally popular in Los Angeles due to frequent ICE raids, the app surged to top rankings in Appleâ€™s U.S. App Store following Bondiâ€™s comments.
- The app shares ICE sighting locations within a five-mile radius without collecting or storing any user data, enhancing privacy for its users.

items.title: Figma Prepares for Potential $1.5B IPO
items.summary:
*Figma has filed for an IPO, possibly raising up to $1.5 billion.*
- The company's **2024 revenue** was $749 million, with **2025 growth** continuing strong.
- Despite investments in AI and market competition, Figma's financial stability and control structure bolster its IPO prospects.

items.title: Road to Battlefield: Central Eurasiaâ€™s gateway to TechCrunch Startup Battlefield
X Pilots AI-Generated Community Notes
items.summary:
- The social platform X is piloting a new feature allowing AI chatbots to generate Community Notes, which add context to posts using AI tools like Grok, while still requiring human vetting to ensure accuracy.  
- Community Notes have inspired similar community fact-checking efforts on Meta, TikTok, and YouTube, leveraging crowdsourced inputs instead of traditional fact-checking programs.  
- Researchers recommend a hybrid approach where humans work alongside AI to improve note quality and critical thinking, but concerns remain about AI hallucinations, sycophantic outputs, and potential overload of human raters.

items.title: Catalio Capital Closes $400M Fund IV
items.summary:
* Catalio Capital Management announced the closing of its **$400 million Fund IV**, focusing on **healthcare and biotech startups**.
* Since founding in 2020, the firm has made over **100 investments**, including companies like PinkDx and Superluminal Medicines.
* The biotech market faced a significant **downturn last year**, with a sharp decline in funding and IPO activity, reflecting broader industry challenges.

items.title: Googleâ€™s data center energy use doubled in 4 years
items.summary:
- *Googleâ€™s data centers* increased their electricity consumption from 14.4M MWh in 2020 to 30.8M MWh in 2024, *more than doubling* in four years.
- Despite efforts to improve efficiency and a commitment to *100% carbon-free energy*, Google faces challenges due to its rapid growth, with *95.8% of electricity* still powering data centers.
- The company is investing in *renewables, geothermal, nuclear fusion*, and *microreactors* to meet energy demands while striving for *around-the-clock* clean power supply.

items.title: Automattic puts Tumblr migration to WordPress on hold
Winning capital for your AI startup? Kleida Martiro is leading the conversation at TechCrunch All Stage
items.summary: *Kleida Martiro*, a seasoned operator and investor, will lead a session on how *AI-native startups* can attract the right *funding* and communicate their growth story effectively.* The event* in Boston on July 15 will provide *tactical advice* for founders building AI, emphasizing alignment with *forward-thinking investors*. Attendees can benefit from Insider tips, network opportunities, and discounted passes to stay ahead in the competitive AI funding landscape.

items.title: Nothing releases its first over-the-ear headphones, the $299 Headphone (1)
items.summary:
- London-based *Nothing* launches its first over-the-ear headphones, *Headphone (1)*, priced at **$299** and designed with British audio brand KEF.  
- Features include *adaptive noise cancelling*, transparent modes, adaptive bass enhancement, immersive spatial audio with dynamic head tracking, and tactile buttons including a volume roller and AI assistant trigger.  
- The headphones offer up to **80 hours** battery life (35 with ANC), comfort for long wear, but are somewhat bulky and heavy, available for preorder starting July 4, 2025 in the US, UK, and more.

items.title: The electric Hummer nears F-150 Lightning sales despite cost gap
items.author: Sean Oâ€™Kane
items.summary:
- General Motors sold 4,508 electric Hummer vehicles in Q2 2025, closely rivaling the Ford F-150 Lightning despite Hummer's higher price.  
- GM's EV sales increased 111% year-over-year with new models and strong commercial van sales, contrasting with Fordâ€™s 31% drop in EV sales.  
- The EV market faces challenges as federal tax incentives wane, with even brands like Hyundai and Tesla seeing sales declines; Ford plans a new low-cost EV by 2027.

items.title: Nothing's First Over-the-Ear Headphones Launch
items.summary:
- *Nothing* has unveiled its first over-the-ear headphones, designed in collaboration with *KEF*. 
- The **aluminum and transparent** design features *adaptive noise canceling*, *bass enhancement*, and *spatial audio* for $299. 
- Interestingly, the *buttons* on these headphones might be the most impressive feature.
